    "Question": {
      "content": "The vector form of the third equation of motion has how many quadratic forms?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "8",
        "3",
        "1",
        "6"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "1"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='color: var(--explainColor); background: var(--explainBg); padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--strongColor);'>\n<h4 style='color: var(--strongColor); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 15px;'>Third Equation of Motion</h4>\n<p>The third equation of motion is \\(v^2 = u^2 + 2as\\).</p>\n<p>In vector form, this becomes a scalar equation (dot product of vectors). It contains one quadratic term (\\(v^2\\) and \\(u^2\\) are scalar magnitudes). The equation as a whole is quadratic in nature but represents a single quadratic relationship.</p>\n<p>Thus, it has <strong>1 quadratic form</strong>.</p>\n</div>"
    }
  },
